article_text:
Private-equity firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts will acquire Internet Brands from Hellman & Friedman and JMI Equity, the companies said Tuesday without disclosing a purchase price.

The New York Times reported the deal is worth $1.1 billion. Hellman & Friedman and JMI Equity bought Internet Brands in 2010 for about $640 million.
